1
00:00:54,722 --> 00:00:57,141
EPISODE 2

2
00:01:15,159 --> 00:01:16,827
TRANQUILIZER

3
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:27,296
DO EUN-HYUK

4
00:01:28,839 --> 00:01:29,715
Hello?

5
00:01:30,591 --> 00:01:31,467
Seol-ah.

6
00:01:33,469 --> 00:01:34,303
Where are you right now?

7
00:01:35,179 --> 00:01:36,347
Why?

8
00:01:37,932 --> 00:01:38,891
Seung-jae…

9
00:01:41,977 --> 00:01:43,145
was in an accident.

10
00:01:45,314 --> 00:01:46,899
Can you come to the dock right now?

11
00:01:58,661 --> 00:02:00,329
I think someone died.

12
00:02:00,412 --> 00:02:01,372
Oh, no.

13
00:02:38,659 --> 00:02:39,910
It's him.

14
00:02:44,915 --> 00:02:45,958
He was my fiancé.

15
00:02:47,877 --> 00:02:48,836
Did you already know?

16
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:52,131
That he canceled his policy
before he died?

17
00:02:52,965 --> 00:02:53,799
Yes.

18
00:02:56,677 --> 00:02:57,595
What a shame.

19
00:02:57,678 --> 00:02:59,513
If he hadn't canceled it,

20
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:02,433
you could've held 700 million won
in your hands.

21
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:04,059
You must have a lot of time on your hands

22
00:03:05,227 --> 00:03:07,479
to investigate a canceled policy.

23
00:03:08,606 --> 00:03:10,024
You couldn't receive the death benefit,

24
00:03:10,608 --> 00:03:14,028
but the 200 million won premium
was returned to Mr. Yoon's account.

25
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:17,531
And you're assuming
that money came my way?

26
00:03:19,450 --> 00:03:22,870
You think I killed my fiancé
for a measly 200 million won?

27
00:03:25,372 --> 00:03:26,790
Tell me.

28
00:03:26,874 --> 00:03:30,836
What does his accident
have to do with what happened to Ms. Kim?

29
00:03:39,011 --> 00:03:40,471
I can smell it.

30
00:03:42,681 --> 00:03:43,807
The stench of someone…

31
00:03:46,143 --> 00:03:47,853
trading human lives for money.

32
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:52,274
Seol-ah.

33
00:03:55,986 --> 00:03:57,279
What are you doing?

34
00:03:57,363 --> 00:03:58,280
Who are you?

35
00:03:59,114 --> 00:04:00,616
You're the one who interrupted us.

36
00:04:00,699 --> 00:04:02,368
Who do you think you are
to treat Seol-ah--

37
00:04:02,451 --> 00:04:03,285
Don't.

38
00:04:08,582 --> 00:04:10,876
Do you, by any chance,
know Mr. Yoon Seung-jae as well?

39
00:04:11,669 --> 00:04:14,421
I'd like to talk to you.
Can I get your contact number?

40
00:04:20,302 --> 00:04:21,720
I'll give you my business card, then.

41
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:29,228
I'll be waiting.

42
00:04:56,964 --> 00:04:58,132
You didn't eat again, did you?

43
00:04:58,882 --> 00:04:59,800
Give me a minute.

44
00:05:04,972 --> 00:05:06,807
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE
SIU SENIOR MANAGER CHA WOO-SEOK

45
00:05:09,018 --> 00:05:11,228
Why did an SIU investigator
come to see you?

46
00:05:12,688 --> 00:05:13,897
And what was all that about Seung-jae?

47
00:05:14,898 --> 00:05:18,193
It seems Kim Yun-ji and Seung-jae
had insurance with that company.

48
00:05:19,153 --> 00:05:20,279
Insurance?

49
00:05:28,037 --> 00:05:28,871
"Seiren"?

50
00:05:29,455 --> 00:05:32,791
You know, mermaids that lured sailors
with their singing.

51
00:05:34,293 --> 00:05:36,545
Oh, I think I remember that
from Greek mythology.

52
00:05:38,797 --> 00:05:40,257
I found that story amusing.

53
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:42,301
I wonder why those men

54
00:05:42,384 --> 00:05:45,179
jumped into the water despite knowing
it'd lead to their deaths.

55
00:05:48,015 --> 00:05:49,016
Is that why

56
00:05:49,099 --> 00:05:50,893
you made it your restaurant logo?

57
00:05:51,935 --> 00:05:52,936
Yeah.

58
00:06:02,696 --> 00:06:05,783
Seol-ah doesn't fully open herself.

59
00:06:09,078 --> 00:06:13,082
There are times when she feels unfamiliar,
as if I'm seeing her for the first time,

60
00:06:13,832 --> 00:06:15,501
and as if she could vanish one day.

61
00:06:21,423 --> 00:06:22,257
Seung-jae…

62
00:06:24,468 --> 00:06:27,387
are you still worried
she won't accept your proposal?

63
00:06:30,182 --> 00:06:31,016
Actually…

64
00:06:32,726 --> 00:06:34,853
I took out a life insurance policy
with Seol-ah as the beneficiary.

65
00:06:48,408 --> 00:06:49,827
EUN-HYE

66
00:07:34,413 --> 00:07:35,914
KIM YUN-JI
AUCTIONEER AT ROYAL AUCTION

67
00:07:35,998 --> 00:07:38,333
DATE OF DEATH: AUGUST 26, 2025
POLICY ISSUE DATE: AUGUST 10, 2023

68
00:07:38,417 --> 00:07:40,544
PUSHED? ACCIDENT? SUICIDE?
TIP CALL BEFORE DEATH

69
00:07:42,087 --> 00:07:45,841
What does his accident
have to do with what happened to Yun-ji?

70
00:07:45,924 --> 00:07:47,634
YOON SEUNG-JAE, OWNER OF THE GALLERY
DATE OF DEATH: AUGUST 17, 2025

71
00:07:47,718 --> 00:07:49,428
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH
CHEONGYANG RIVER YACHT ACCIDENT: DROWNED?

72
00:07:52,181 --> 00:07:54,683
And you're assuming
that money came my way?

73
00:07:56,810 --> 00:08:00,439
You think I killed my fiancé
for a measly 200 million won?

74
00:08:17,998 --> 00:08:19,833
These are the newly arrived pieces.

75
00:08:24,087 --> 00:08:25,756
And the condition report for these?

76
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:28,217
I found the file on Ms. Kim's computer.

77
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:29,426
I'll take care of it.

78
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:31,762
I appreciate it, Sang-mi.

79
00:08:31,845 --> 00:08:32,679
Of course.

80
00:08:33,263 --> 00:08:34,139
Also,

81
00:08:34,723 --> 00:08:35,807
about that…

82
00:08:38,101 --> 00:08:39,102
What should we do with it?

83
00:08:42,022 --> 00:08:43,565
COMMUNITY CHAT SEARCH
RISK LIFE FOR MONEY

84
00:08:43,649 --> 00:08:45,359
Anyone willing to risk their life
for money?

85
00:08:46,652 --> 00:08:47,694
Must be in Cheongun.

86
00:08:47,778 --> 00:08:50,489
Recruiting a hitter
with a clean insurance record.

87
00:08:51,365 --> 00:08:52,449
What's the rate?

88
00:08:53,242 --> 00:08:55,035
If we go easy,
about three million won per person.

89
00:08:56,245 --> 00:08:57,120
I'm in.

90
00:08:57,871 --> 00:08:58,872
What car do you have?

91
00:08:58,956 --> 00:09:00,582
It's less suspicious if it's expensive.

92
00:09:04,127 --> 00:09:05,629
It's a foreign-made car, of course.

93
00:09:06,463 --> 00:09:08,882
Yes, I'll get back to you shortly.

94
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,261
-Mr. Cha.
-Yeah?

95
00:09:12,344 --> 00:09:15,389
Ms. Kim Yun-ji's family
had no idea about her insurance policy.

96
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,023
Take all the time you need.

97
00:09:26,525 --> 00:09:27,401
Once you get in touch,

98
00:09:28,068 --> 00:09:30,696
I'll make sure the insurance payout
is processed smoothly.

99
00:09:32,990 --> 00:09:34,157
Thank you.

100
00:09:35,242 --> 00:09:36,326
Thank you, but…

101
00:09:37,619 --> 00:09:39,997
I'd pay a hundred times that amount

102
00:09:41,415 --> 00:09:43,542
if it'd bring my child back.

103
00:09:44,418 --> 00:09:46,670
My precious daughter is gone.

104
00:09:47,379 --> 00:09:49,339
What's the point of any of this?

105
00:10:08,066 --> 00:10:08,984
I'll take that.

106
00:10:10,027 --> 00:10:11,486
It's heavy.

107
00:10:11,570 --> 00:10:12,696
I'm sorry for the trouble.

108
00:10:13,989 --> 00:10:15,073
Let me carry it for you.

109
00:10:19,036 --> 00:10:20,537
He's from the insurance company.

110
00:10:22,831 --> 00:10:23,707
Where should I put it?

111
00:10:24,291 --> 00:10:25,208
This way, please.

112
00:10:40,891 --> 00:10:42,809
It feels like she'll be back any moment,

113
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:45,145
so I left everything just as it is.

114
00:10:46,438 --> 00:10:47,397
Over here, please.

115
00:10:56,114 --> 00:10:58,325
There are a lot of company documents.

116
00:10:58,408 --> 00:11:00,911
You can take them with you
if you need them.

117
00:11:01,828 --> 00:11:03,330
Okay, I will.

118
00:11:04,289 --> 00:11:05,290
All right, then.

119
00:11:05,957 --> 00:11:07,084
Take a look around.

120
00:11:08,794 --> 00:11:10,962
I'll prepare some tea for you
in the living room.

121
00:11:54,131 --> 00:11:55,715
H2 2025 GLOBAL ART TRENDS REPORT

122
00:12:29,082 --> 00:12:30,792
Can you step out for a bit?

123
00:12:31,918 --> 00:12:32,752
Why?

124
00:12:32,836 --> 00:12:34,880
Do you want to rummage on your own?

125
00:12:34,963 --> 00:12:36,590
Didn't you hear what her mother said?

126
00:12:37,299 --> 00:12:39,134
She told me to take the company documents.

127
00:12:59,696 --> 00:13:02,574
HAN SEOL-AH BUSINESS TRIP

128
00:13:02,657 --> 00:13:04,576
HAN SEOL-AH MEETING
WITH SU GALLERY MANAGER

129
00:13:06,286 --> 00:13:08,663
HAN SEOL-AH ON LEAVE

130
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:13,376
OUT OF THE OFFICE ALL DAY
MAYBE A VIP CLIENT MEETING?

131
00:13:21,551 --> 00:13:24,721
She didn't smile once
after joining Royal Auction.

132
00:13:25,555 --> 00:13:27,015
I thought it was rather strange

133
00:13:27,098 --> 00:13:29,726
when she left the TV station

134
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:32,020
and suddenly decided to work
at an auction house.

135
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:36,650
What kind of person

136
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:39,486
was Ms. Kim at work?

137
00:13:45,492 --> 00:13:47,160
She was hard-working.

138
00:13:48,870 --> 00:13:50,622
I heard she was about to get promoted.

139
00:13:52,165 --> 00:13:53,458
I just don't understand.

140
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,127
When a suicide takes place at a company,

141
00:13:57,295 --> 00:13:58,547
there's usually a message behind it.

142
00:13:59,422 --> 00:14:02,676
For example, workplace bullying,
conflict between colleagues,

143
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:03,593
or being wronged.

144
00:14:03,677 --> 00:14:05,720
But you're saying
it was none of these things.

145
00:14:06,304 --> 00:14:07,681
Then I wonder what it was.

146
00:14:08,807 --> 00:14:10,892
I don't know
everyone's personal matters at work.

147
00:14:14,938 --> 00:14:18,108
Do you have any idea
what it could've been?

148
00:14:19,818 --> 00:14:20,652
There's one thing…

149
00:14:22,779 --> 00:14:24,322
that comes to mind.

150
00:14:37,294 --> 00:14:39,796
Why are you out all night these days?

151
00:14:40,839 --> 00:14:43,300
Get up and have a bite to eat
before you sleep.

152
00:14:55,854 --> 00:14:56,730
Are you…

153
00:14:57,981 --> 00:14:59,608
seeing that man again?

154
00:15:01,484 --> 00:15:02,819
Were you with him?

155
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:07,115
What's wrong, Yun-ji?

156
00:15:11,745 --> 00:15:14,581
Do you know the man Yun-ji was seeing?

157
00:15:19,586 --> 00:15:20,879
A man?

158
00:15:21,588 --> 00:15:23,632
I'm her mother, but I don't know anything.

159
00:15:26,384 --> 00:15:28,386
I don't know why
she was suffering so much,

160
00:15:29,137 --> 00:15:31,681
or why she chose to end things.

161
00:15:31,765 --> 00:15:32,974
ASSOCIATE AUCTIONEER KIM YUN-JI

162
00:15:33,058 --> 00:15:36,811
I'm her mother, but I don't know anything.

163
00:15:42,901 --> 00:15:44,819
I'm sure you went through
everything at work.

164
00:15:46,905 --> 00:15:49,199
Did you come to check
if she left something at home?

165
00:15:49,783 --> 00:15:51,368
You came to check first,

166
00:15:51,451 --> 00:15:52,702
but I guess you didn't find anything.

167
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:54,746
You want to know what I found?

168
00:15:55,664 --> 00:15:56,665
I could tell you.

169
00:15:57,290 --> 00:15:58,625
Keep it to yourself.

170
00:15:58,708 --> 00:16:00,960
I don't care what you came here to do,

171
00:16:01,044 --> 00:16:04,381
but I find it offensive to be questioned
before a mother who lost her daughter.

172
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:06,883
Shouldn't you be more cooperative
as her immediate supervisor?

173
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:09,469
I've already cooperated with the police.

174
00:16:09,552 --> 00:16:11,638
And I have no interest
in prying into the private life

175
00:16:12,180 --> 00:16:13,139
of the deceased.

176
00:16:13,932 --> 00:16:15,684
I'm trying to find out

177
00:16:17,143 --> 00:16:18,728
whether or not it was a wrongful death.

178
00:16:20,605 --> 00:16:21,690
Wrongful death?

179
00:16:25,819 --> 00:16:26,986
What about wrongful suspicion?

180
00:16:28,738 --> 00:16:31,574
You never know
who the real victim might be.

181
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:12,365
VIOLENT CRIMES UNIT 1

182
00:17:13,825 --> 00:17:14,868
CALL LOG
NAME: KIM YUN-JI

183
00:17:16,578 --> 00:17:18,329
YOON SEUNG-JAE

184
00:17:18,913 --> 00:17:20,290
YOON SEUNG-JAE

185
00:17:24,919 --> 00:17:26,045
Yoon Seung-jae.

186
00:17:26,671 --> 00:17:27,797
Yoon Seung-jae.

187
00:17:28,506 --> 00:17:29,716
Yoon Seung-jae again.

188
00:17:31,718 --> 00:17:33,928
Hey, Ggong.
You've heard of Yoon Seung-jae, right?

189
00:17:34,012 --> 00:17:37,015
Yes, I left the Cheongun Police Station
investigation report on your desk.

190
00:17:37,557 --> 00:17:38,558
Investigation report?

191
00:17:40,810 --> 00:17:42,812
GANGNAM "A CLUB" VIP NARCOTICS CASE
GANGHA POLICE STATION

192
00:17:45,648 --> 00:17:49,068
YOON SEUNG-JAE DEATH CASE

193
00:17:52,489 --> 00:17:56,284
BODY FOUND FLOATING IN WATER
BODY IDENTIFIED BY FIANCÉE (HAN SEOL-AH)

194
00:18:09,214 --> 00:18:11,424
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

195
00:18:11,508 --> 00:18:13,843
2025 CERTIFIED
INSURANCE FRAUD INVESTIGATOR

196
00:18:19,474 --> 00:18:21,726
Don't tell me he hasn't come to work yet.

197
00:18:22,268 --> 00:18:24,521
Does he not know the quarter-end
is right around the corner?

198
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:26,481
That little punk.

199
00:18:27,065 --> 00:18:28,066
Hey, Cha.

200
00:18:28,942 --> 00:18:30,109
Where the hell are you?!

201
00:18:32,695 --> 00:18:33,947
Oh, I see.

202
00:18:34,030 --> 00:18:36,407
Of course, you have to spend money.

203
00:18:37,659 --> 00:18:39,369
Right, right. Be careful, okay?

204
00:18:40,745 --> 00:18:41,579
What did he say?

205
00:18:41,663 --> 00:18:43,122
He's bringing in a big one.

206
00:18:46,334 --> 00:18:49,128
I'm so done being stuck in this office.

207
00:18:49,212 --> 00:18:50,630
I'm getting out of here!

208
00:18:50,713 --> 00:18:51,548
I can do this!

209
00:18:53,049 --> 00:18:54,133
"The Purpose of Insurance."

210
00:19:04,727 --> 00:19:09,649
CHEONGUN, WHERE LIFE IS GOOD

211
00:19:09,732 --> 00:19:11,609
All right, the backers are here and ready.

212
00:19:11,693 --> 00:19:12,527
Where are you, Mr. Hitter?

213
00:19:13,236 --> 00:19:14,904
I'm 500 meters behind.

214
00:19:15,446 --> 00:19:16,614
This is your first time, right?

215
00:19:16,698 --> 00:19:19,242
I'll go straight,
then turn right, and brake hard,

216
00:19:19,325 --> 00:19:21,035
so be bold and don't hold back.

217
00:19:21,119 --> 00:19:22,412
Just ram into us, okay?

218
00:19:23,872 --> 00:19:25,498
But you're in a compact car.

219
00:19:25,582 --> 00:19:28,459
Just go for it. We won't die.

220
00:19:29,711 --> 00:19:31,880
I'll hit you full force, then.

221
00:19:31,963 --> 00:19:32,839
Okay.

222
00:19:33,464 --> 00:19:34,591
What's your plate number again?

223
00:19:35,174 --> 00:19:36,259
It's 7622.

224
00:19:36,342 --> 00:19:38,094
Got it.

225
00:19:38,177 --> 00:19:39,345
Follow us, but don't make it obvious.

226
00:19:39,888 --> 00:19:40,972
Hey, let's go.

227
00:19:54,235 --> 00:19:55,778
What's taking him so long?

228
00:19:57,447 --> 00:19:59,824
Damn it, why isn't Cha Woo-seok here yet?

229
00:20:00,909 --> 00:20:04,495
-Hey, move over, will you?
-Sit still, for crying out loud.

230
00:20:04,579 --> 00:20:06,039
-Why isn't he coming?
-Why is it so tight in here?

231
00:20:06,122 --> 00:20:07,498
Where is he?

232
00:20:08,082 --> 00:20:10,209
Hey, where are you?
You said you had a foreign-made car.

233
00:20:10,793 --> 00:20:12,128
I do.

234
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:13,880
It's just a bit big.

235
00:20:13,963 --> 00:20:15,298
What the hell are you saying?

236
00:20:28,895 --> 00:20:30,355
What the hell? It's 7622!

237
00:20:32,106 --> 00:20:33,024
That's him!

238
00:20:33,107 --> 00:20:35,234
-Hey, step on it!
-What the hell?

239
00:20:35,818 --> 00:20:37,362
What the hell is with him?

240
00:20:37,445 --> 00:20:39,072
-Just go!
-Go!

241
00:20:39,155 --> 00:20:40,490
-Speed it up!
-Step on it!

242
00:20:41,991 --> 00:20:43,534
Go faster!

243
00:20:44,077 --> 00:20:45,662
Step on it already!

244
00:20:45,745 --> 00:20:47,538
I told you to lose some weight!

245
00:20:47,622 --> 00:20:49,582
-He's going to hit us!
-Go, go, go!

246
00:20:52,168 --> 00:20:53,878
Hey, move to the side!

247
00:20:54,921 --> 00:20:56,339
I told you to lose some weight, idiot!

248
00:20:56,422 --> 00:20:57,298
Hey!

249
00:20:57,382 --> 00:20:59,509
You crazy bastard! Stop right now!

250
00:21:00,009 --> 00:21:01,844
-Hey!
-Step on it!

251
00:21:01,928 --> 00:21:03,221
He's closing in!

252
00:21:03,304 --> 00:21:05,390
-Go faster!
-He's going to hit us!

253
00:21:07,517 --> 00:21:09,519
Go faster, come on!

254
00:21:09,602 --> 00:21:11,229
Speed up!

255
00:21:11,312 --> 00:21:12,522
Step on it!

256
00:21:14,565 --> 00:21:16,317
-Go faster!
-He's coming!

257
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:18,444
Step on it!

258
00:21:20,822 --> 00:21:23,032
This is my goddamn car!

259
00:21:24,909 --> 00:21:26,536
-Watch it!
-Holy crap!

260
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:33,126
Oh, jeez.

261
00:21:39,716 --> 00:21:40,800
Damn it.

262
00:21:42,885 --> 00:21:44,470
Man, I feel like I'm going to die.

263
00:21:44,554 --> 00:21:46,222
Oh, man.

264
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:47,557
What are you all looking at?

265
00:21:51,394 --> 00:21:52,979
It's nothing. Go back inside.

266
00:21:54,355 --> 00:21:55,481
Oh, dear.

267
00:21:55,565 --> 00:21:57,066
I was going to hit you from behind,

268
00:21:57,150 --> 00:21:59,027
but you crashed into the truck
in front of you.

269
00:21:59,110 --> 00:22:00,194
Hey.

270
00:22:00,278 --> 00:22:01,988
Were you trying to kill or something?

271
00:22:02,071 --> 00:22:03,031
Yeah.

272
00:22:03,114 --> 00:22:05,199
-How'd you know?
-Hey.

273
00:22:05,783 --> 00:22:06,659
Hey.

274
00:22:06,743 --> 00:22:08,703
Oh, let me introduce you to each other.

275
00:22:09,370 --> 00:22:12,206
This is Detective Kim
from Cheongun Police Station.

276
00:22:12,290 --> 00:22:14,834
And this is the Cheongun Family Gang,

277
00:22:14,917 --> 00:22:16,210
an insurance fraud ring.

278
00:22:16,794 --> 00:22:18,087
Oh, I see.

279
00:22:20,089 --> 00:22:21,215
An insurance fraud ring, huh?

280
00:22:21,299 --> 00:22:23,509
-Cops?
-Nice to meet you.

281
00:22:23,593 --> 00:22:26,429
-All right, let's go.
-That hurts!

282
00:22:28,389 --> 00:22:30,850
-Come on.
-That hurts!

283
00:22:30,933 --> 00:22:32,977
-See you.
-Go already.

284
00:22:34,187 --> 00:22:35,772
No wonder you wanted to meet

285
00:22:35,855 --> 00:22:37,857
at such a random place
instead of the station.

286
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:41,944
Here.

287
00:22:44,072 --> 00:22:45,615
Files on all the scams
they've pulled off so far

288
00:22:45,698 --> 00:22:47,158
and CCTV footage.

289
00:22:47,241 --> 00:22:48,409
Man.

290
00:22:48,493 --> 00:22:49,535
This is just what I needed.

291
00:22:49,619 --> 00:22:51,496
A guy like you
should've stayed on as a detective.

292
00:22:53,247 --> 00:22:54,957
Let me show you
what you asked me to look into.

293
00:22:56,417 --> 00:22:59,003
When I got there, he was already dead.

294
00:22:59,712 --> 00:23:00,713
It was an accidental death.

295
00:23:01,756 --> 00:23:03,925
Are you sure Yoon Seung-jae
was alone on the yacht?

296
00:23:04,008 --> 00:23:04,842
Yeah.

297
00:23:04,926 --> 00:23:08,679
There were a lot of witnesses,
including the dock manager and fishermen.

298
00:23:09,889 --> 00:23:11,891
-Then the autopsy results must also--
-Death by drowning.

299
00:23:12,517 --> 00:23:15,478
I think he accidentally fell overboard
and struck the propellers.

300
00:23:16,854 --> 00:23:18,731
The case itself isn't strange,

301
00:23:18,815 --> 00:23:20,191
but that woman was a bit…

302
00:23:22,151 --> 00:23:23,194
Here it is.

303
00:23:25,696 --> 00:23:28,658
His family was overseas at the time,

304
00:23:28,741 --> 00:23:30,910
so his fiancée came to identify the body.

305
00:23:32,578 --> 00:23:35,123
I worried she might pass out
because the body was severely damaged,

306
00:23:35,206 --> 00:23:36,791
but she didn't even bat an eye.

307
00:24:33,431 --> 00:24:34,265
Here.

308
00:24:35,474 --> 00:24:37,185
I canceled the insurance policy,

309
00:24:37,768 --> 00:24:38,769
so don't worry.

310
00:25:03,169 --> 00:25:05,796
CHAIR KIM

311
00:25:07,381 --> 00:25:08,216
I always make sure

312
00:25:09,217 --> 00:25:13,054
to include steamed sea bream
on my father's ancestral table.

313
00:25:13,804 --> 00:25:15,139
He must've liked it.

314
00:25:16,057 --> 00:25:17,516
He didn't because it was too fishy.

315
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:19,227
I only make it because I want to eat it.

316
00:25:22,104 --> 00:25:22,939
Try some.

317
00:25:24,357 --> 00:25:26,442
Are you sure you didn't make it for me?

318
00:25:27,652 --> 00:25:29,070
Sharp as ever.

319
00:25:29,946 --> 00:25:33,574
Back when I used to bring raw fish
to Artist Han's studio,

320
00:25:33,658 --> 00:25:35,576
you were always the most excited.

321
00:25:35,660 --> 00:25:39,330
Even at a young age, you ate everything,
including sea squirt and sea cucumber.

322
00:25:41,082 --> 00:25:42,541
You seem to remember everything.

323
00:25:43,793 --> 00:25:46,003
You made the right call
visiting Ms. Kim's family.

324
00:25:47,338 --> 00:25:50,216
It takes that kind of thinking
to protect a company.

325
00:25:50,883 --> 00:25:54,804
Workplace bullying
is such a big topic these days.

326
00:25:56,180 --> 00:25:58,349
-How did you--
-They called to say thank you.

327
00:25:58,933 --> 00:26:01,477
Did you know her father
works at the National Tax Service?

328
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:05,064
If he set his mind to it,
he could easily take down our company.

329
00:26:07,692 --> 00:26:10,611
From what I've heard, her death seems to
have been caused by personal matters.

330
00:26:10,695 --> 00:26:13,614
Her mother didn't harbor
any resentment toward us.

331
00:26:13,698 --> 00:26:16,242
She appeared to be having
a hard time though.

332
00:26:17,034 --> 00:26:18,536
You're having a hard time too.

333
00:26:19,537 --> 00:26:21,163
I heard you lost your fiancé
in an accident.

334
00:26:21,747 --> 00:26:23,082
If something like that happened,

335
00:26:23,749 --> 00:26:26,294
you should've told me
and taken some time off.

336
00:26:28,713 --> 00:26:31,799
It was better for me to focus on work.

337
00:26:35,136 --> 00:26:36,345
You poor thing.

338
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:43,519
Here, eat up while it's still warm.

339
00:27:47,375 --> 00:27:50,169
I called you earlier.
I'm Cha Woo-seok, an SIU investigator.

340
00:27:51,420 --> 00:27:52,671
What is this about?

341
00:27:52,755 --> 00:27:55,383
I'm investigating matters
involving Mr. Yoon Seung-jae's insurance.

342
00:27:56,801 --> 00:27:58,344
I believe he had a fiancée?

343
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:00,596
Yes, I know her.

344
00:28:01,305 --> 00:28:02,348
Seol-ah.

345
00:28:03,516 --> 00:28:04,517
Do you happen to know

346
00:28:05,351 --> 00:28:06,811
Ms. Kim Yun-ji as well?

347
00:28:07,895 --> 00:28:08,771
Who?

348
00:28:12,691 --> 00:28:13,526
This person.

349
00:28:14,902 --> 00:28:16,028
Oh, I've seen her before.

350
00:28:16,112 --> 00:28:18,072
I remember her
because she's been coming by often.

351
00:28:18,906 --> 00:28:20,783
Ms. Kim Yun-ji has been here?

352
00:28:20,866 --> 00:28:21,909
What for?

353
00:28:21,992 --> 00:28:23,744
I wouldn't know.

354
00:28:28,707 --> 00:28:30,835
What was her relationship with Mr. Yoon?

355
00:28:30,918 --> 00:28:32,711
Did it look like
they'd known each other long?

356
00:28:32,795 --> 00:28:34,713
They didn't seem close.

357
00:28:34,797 --> 00:28:37,341
Mr. Yoon didn't seem that fond of her.

358
00:28:39,260 --> 00:28:40,428
When was her last visit?

359
00:28:42,263 --> 00:28:44,390
The day before Mr. Yoon's accident.

360
00:28:44,473 --> 00:28:46,434
She came by again

361
00:28:46,517 --> 00:28:49,728
and waited until we closed,
saying she had something to tell him.

362
00:28:53,107 --> 00:28:54,108
She sat over there.

363
00:30:12,811 --> 00:30:15,856
When I got there, he was already dead.

364
00:30:15,940 --> 00:30:17,233
It was an accidental death.

365
00:30:38,587 --> 00:30:41,215
Kim Yun-ji and Yoon Seung-jae met,

366
00:30:42,383 --> 00:30:44,051
and they both died

367
00:30:45,553 --> 00:30:46,720
in just ten days.

368
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:51,350
I didn't know you were so competent.

369
00:30:54,228 --> 00:30:56,272
It's normal for the police
to have reasonable suspicions.

370
00:30:56,772 --> 00:30:58,107
But why would an SIU investigator

371
00:30:58,649 --> 00:31:01,151
chase after a case
where a payout was never made?

372
00:31:03,153 --> 00:31:04,530
That's the problem with you, Seong-il.

373
00:31:05,406 --> 00:31:06,907
You lack imagination.

374
00:31:08,033 --> 00:31:09,159
You think this was the first time?

375
00:31:10,202 --> 00:31:11,745
This is why you're always one step behind.

376
00:31:14,123 --> 00:31:16,458
Ever thought that your imagination
might be the problem?

377
00:31:17,042 --> 00:31:18,794
Like the delusion
about your sister's death

378
00:31:19,628 --> 00:31:20,462
being a murder.

379
00:31:23,716 --> 00:31:26,176
As the detective in charge,
you don't want to admit incompetence,

380
00:31:26,260 --> 00:31:27,511
yet you want peace of mind.

381
00:31:28,804 --> 00:31:29,638
Yeah.

382
00:31:30,472 --> 00:31:31,599
I get it.

383
00:31:32,933 --> 00:31:34,101
But are you really at peace?

384
00:32:05,716 --> 00:32:07,009
What are you thinking about?

385
00:32:08,302 --> 00:32:10,179
Stop worrying about me.

386
00:32:10,262 --> 00:32:11,388
I'm not.

387
00:32:11,472 --> 00:32:13,682
You are. It's written all over your face.

388
00:32:13,766 --> 00:32:15,934
I didn't lie like my friends did

389
00:32:16,018 --> 00:32:17,770
and was honest about
taking a trip with my boyfriend.

390
00:32:19,563 --> 00:32:21,607
Jeez, when did you grow up?

391
00:32:21,690 --> 00:32:23,108
I think I'll get married before you.

392
00:32:25,903 --> 00:32:26,945
Ms. Cha Woo-hee.

393
00:32:27,613 --> 00:32:29,490
Marriage already? Control yourself.

394
00:33:16,495 --> 00:33:17,663
I'll have what she's having.

395
00:33:42,896 --> 00:33:45,607
Did you know Kim Yun-ji went to see
Yoon Seung-jae at his restaurant?

396
00:33:48,277 --> 00:33:49,528
On the day before the accident, at that.

397
00:33:53,699 --> 00:33:54,825
So?

398
00:33:56,785 --> 00:33:58,120
Why did those two meet?

399
00:34:00,831 --> 00:34:03,375
You can't know everything about someone,
no matter how close you are to them.

400
00:34:06,128 --> 00:34:07,463
So you have no idea?

401
00:34:09,548 --> 00:34:11,049
Then what could it be?

402
00:34:12,134 --> 00:34:15,888
What reason was there for your fiancé
and colleague to meet secretly?

403
00:34:17,723 --> 00:34:19,808
It didn't seem like
they were just acquaintances.

404
00:34:21,477 --> 00:34:22,478
Were they

405
00:34:23,604 --> 00:34:25,481
involved or something?

406
00:34:35,532 --> 00:34:36,950
You kill out of love,

407
00:34:37,659 --> 00:34:40,662
you kill out of hate, and you want to kill
as much as you love.

408
00:34:42,873 --> 00:34:44,958
The most common motive for murder
is love affairs.

409
00:34:47,795 --> 00:34:48,629
Love affairs?

410
00:34:49,922 --> 00:34:51,048
Not a fan of that theory?

411
00:34:51,632 --> 00:34:53,592
Then what about
premeditated murder for money?

412
00:34:58,555 --> 00:35:00,891
Do you know what insurance scammers
have in common?

413
00:35:02,601 --> 00:35:04,770
Once they've had a taste of money,
they want more.

414
00:35:04,853 --> 00:35:06,939
They want bigger money
through easier means.

415
00:35:07,022 --> 00:35:10,609
Then things escalate, and they get bolder,
so bold that people start to notice.

416
00:35:12,903 --> 00:35:14,863
-What does that have to do with--
-Ms. Han Seol-ah.

417
00:35:16,615 --> 00:35:17,991
I'm investigating a tip I received.

418
00:35:19,243 --> 00:35:22,371
A tip claiming that Yoon Seung-jae's death
was a case of murder-for-insurance.

419
00:35:28,752 --> 00:35:30,295
I see Ms. Kim Yun-ji gave you the tip.

420
00:35:31,588 --> 00:35:33,173
I was supposed to meet her that night.

421
00:35:34,466 --> 00:35:35,425
But she goes and commits suicide?

422
00:35:37,970 --> 00:35:39,221
That makes no sense at all.

423
00:35:43,141 --> 00:35:44,685
Stop playing detective.

424
00:35:45,936 --> 00:35:48,272
I never received any insurance payout,

425
00:35:48,355 --> 00:35:49,189
which means

426
00:35:50,399 --> 00:35:52,317
I'm not the subject of your investigation.

427
00:35:54,862 --> 00:35:56,196
I guess I'll find the answer
if I dig deeper.

428
00:35:59,867 --> 00:36:01,451
What is it that you really want to know?

429
00:36:05,789 --> 00:36:07,833
Your fiancé and Kim Yun-ji.

430
00:36:12,713 --> 00:36:13,714
Did you kill them?

431
00:37:16,234 --> 00:37:20,030
HAN SEOL-AH IN CHEONGUN CITY

432
00:37:24,826 --> 00:37:27,746
HAN SEOL-AH, KIM YUN-JI, YOON SEUNG-JAE

433
00:37:28,330 --> 00:37:29,373
A love triangle?

434
00:37:29,456 --> 00:37:30,707
I don't think Han Seol-ah knew.

435
00:37:32,751 --> 00:37:33,627
Really?

436
00:37:34,419 --> 00:37:35,629
Micro expressions.

437
00:37:37,589 --> 00:37:39,174
No matter how good your poker face is,

438
00:37:39,800 --> 00:37:42,052
you can't hide fleeting expressions.

439
00:37:43,720 --> 00:37:44,680
She didn't know.

440
00:37:46,890 --> 00:37:49,309
And there's no way to find out
since they're both dead.

441
00:37:50,227 --> 00:37:51,353
What really happened?

442
00:37:52,771 --> 00:37:53,814
But you know,

443
00:37:54,898 --> 00:37:57,651
when I asked if she killed them,
she was surprisingly unshaken.

444
00:37:58,235 --> 00:37:59,152
It's one or the other.

445
00:38:00,278 --> 00:38:01,321
Either she's innocent,

446
00:38:01,905 --> 00:38:03,865
or she's completely deceiving
even herself.

447
00:38:05,117 --> 00:38:07,703
Either way, it was just
attempted insurance fraud, right?

448
00:38:08,996 --> 00:38:11,206
Ju Hyun-su didn't start out
intending to commit murder either.

449
00:38:13,375 --> 00:38:15,711
It started with the insurance payout
from the car accident.

450
00:38:17,045 --> 00:38:19,756
His accident insurance got denied,
so he needed a scapegoat.

451
00:38:22,134 --> 00:38:23,427
And that was my sister.

452
00:38:25,595 --> 00:38:28,807
So you think Han Seol-ah likely received
a payout in the past as well?

453
00:38:30,434 --> 00:38:31,351
Probably.

454
00:38:56,376 --> 00:38:59,212
I heard Ms. Kim died
after an argument with Ms. Han.

455
00:38:59,796 --> 00:39:00,630
Really?

456
00:39:01,590 --> 00:39:04,259
I heard Ms. Han gave Ms. Kim
a really tough time.

457
00:39:28,241 --> 00:39:31,036
I sensed something might happen
from the moment you tore that painting.

458
00:39:32,245 --> 00:39:33,872
I can't blame her for wanting to die.

459
00:39:35,832 --> 00:39:37,209
I've kept quiet about this,

460
00:39:37,292 --> 00:39:40,754
but Ms. Kim often came to me in tears.

461
00:39:40,837 --> 00:39:41,963
Because of you.

462
00:39:43,465 --> 00:39:44,549
I see.

463
00:39:44,633 --> 00:39:47,135
Then why didn't you do a better job
comforting her?

464
00:39:47,219 --> 00:39:49,596
I guess she couldn't rely on you either.

465
00:39:51,890 --> 00:39:52,808
Whatever.

466
00:39:52,891 --> 00:39:54,726
What's important is public opinion.

467
00:39:56,019 --> 00:39:57,437
The real reason Kim Yun-ji died…

468
00:39:57,521 --> 00:39:59,397
Han Seol-ah constantly bullied Kim Yun-ji…

469
00:39:59,481 --> 00:40:01,900
Rumors about the chief auctioneer
replacement have been floating around…

470
00:40:01,983 --> 00:40:04,152
Ms. Han is Chair Kim's secret daughter?

471
00:40:04,236 --> 00:40:05,445
There's no way.

472
00:40:06,571 --> 00:40:07,989
If you want to sway public opinion,

473
00:40:08,073 --> 00:40:10,075
you should at least use multiple accounts.

474
00:40:11,326 --> 00:40:12,160
What?

475
00:40:12,994 --> 00:40:13,870
What did you say?

476
00:40:18,333 --> 00:40:19,376
Damn it.

477
00:40:19,876 --> 00:40:22,462
She's too damn observant.

478
00:40:23,713 --> 00:40:24,673
For goodness' sake.

479
00:40:35,934 --> 00:40:37,352
A bit higher, please.

480
00:40:42,524 --> 00:40:43,358
Okay.

481
00:40:43,942 --> 00:40:44,943
Next piece.

482
00:40:46,862 --> 00:40:47,737
That's good.

483
00:40:53,201 --> 00:40:54,035
Set the lighting to 20.

484
00:40:56,663 --> 00:40:57,497
Okay, next piece.

485
00:41:07,507 --> 00:41:10,343
-Let's take a ten-minute break.
-Okay.

486
00:41:17,559 --> 00:41:20,228
THE REAL REASON KIM YUN-JI DIED
RUMORS ABOUT CHIEF AUCTIONEER REPLACEMENT

487
00:41:22,147 --> 00:41:24,065
IS IT TRUE THAT MS. HAN IS QUITTING?

488
00:41:25,150 --> 00:41:26,234
What do you think?

489
00:41:28,403 --> 00:41:29,237
About what?

490
00:41:30,238 --> 00:41:33,158
I'm asking how much you can trust
your best friend, Han Seol-ah.

491
00:41:34,784 --> 00:41:36,203
Go back to work.

492
00:41:36,286 --> 00:41:37,913
She scares me now.

493
00:41:37,996 --> 00:41:39,831
I'm worried about you.

494
00:41:41,833 --> 00:41:44,920
Be honest.
You're suspecting her too, aren't you?

495
00:41:48,548 --> 00:41:49,382
Eun-hye.

496
00:41:50,675 --> 00:41:52,093
Seol-ah's the one

497
00:41:52,844 --> 00:41:54,262
who got you this internship.

498
00:41:55,931 --> 00:41:58,183
The scholarships
and training opportunities you got

499
00:41:58,266 --> 00:41:59,517
didn't just happen on their own.

500
00:42:02,938 --> 00:42:04,064
I never asked her for any of that.

501
00:42:04,147 --> 00:42:05,523
Who does she think she is?

502
00:42:06,107 --> 00:42:07,609
She considers us family.

503
00:42:07,692 --> 00:42:08,526
Family?

504
00:42:08,610 --> 00:42:11,529
She's just pretending to care about me
so she can use you.

505
00:42:11,613 --> 00:42:13,323
She's just keeping you around
to make you take photos.

506
00:42:13,406 --> 00:42:15,200
Watch what you say.

507
00:42:25,126 --> 00:42:26,336
This tastes good.

508
00:42:28,797 --> 00:42:31,967
You told me before

509
00:42:32,759 --> 00:42:34,386
that my mom getting money

510
00:42:35,053 --> 00:42:36,846
from me falling ill

511
00:42:37,514 --> 00:42:39,557
wouldn't make her happy,

512
00:42:41,142 --> 00:42:44,854
and that it'd just lead her
further down a bad path.

513
00:42:45,647 --> 00:42:47,607
If I tell the truth,

514
00:42:49,109 --> 00:42:51,069
what will happen to her?

515
00:42:52,445 --> 00:42:53,780
Will she get taken away?

516
00:42:59,744 --> 00:43:00,745
Chae-rin.

517
00:43:02,622 --> 00:43:04,499
The only person who can stop your mom

518
00:43:05,375 --> 00:43:06,251
is you.

519
00:43:07,836 --> 00:43:10,338
And I want to protect you

520
00:43:11,756 --> 00:43:13,049
so you won't hurt anymore.

521
00:43:17,178 --> 00:43:18,847
I'm sorry I couldn't protect you sooner.

522
00:43:25,979 --> 00:43:27,188
I'm fuming.

523
00:43:27,272 --> 00:43:29,482
How much time do you think
Chae-rin's mom will serve?

524
00:43:29,566 --> 00:43:32,485
Can't people like her
just be locked up for good?

525
00:43:32,569 --> 00:43:33,820
What kind of mother is she?

526
00:43:35,030 --> 00:43:37,157
I'm glad Chae-rin finally spoke up,

527
00:43:38,408 --> 00:43:39,743
but I'm not sure about this.

528
00:43:41,328 --> 00:43:42,662
No matter how terrible a mom is,

529
00:43:43,538 --> 00:43:44,956
a child would still miss her.

530
00:43:46,166 --> 00:43:48,418
But still,
we couldn't just leave her like that.

531
00:43:48,501 --> 00:43:49,502
We had to save her.

532
00:43:49,586 --> 00:43:51,755
Did we really save her though?

533
00:43:51,838 --> 00:43:53,757
At least we saved her from the worst.

534
00:43:54,758 --> 00:43:57,469
The world's a crazy place.
All this over money.

535
00:43:58,678 --> 00:44:00,889
I've requested her foster care
and medical support,

536
00:44:00,972 --> 00:44:02,140
so make sure to follow up on it.

537
00:44:02,223 --> 00:44:03,933
I've already prepared
the necessary documents.

538
00:44:09,898 --> 00:44:10,940
Hello, this is Cha Woo-seok.

539
00:44:11,649 --> 00:44:14,861
Mr. Cha, this is the Insurance Fraud
Prevention Team at the KLIA.

540
00:44:14,944 --> 00:44:16,363
It's about your inquiry on Han Seol-ah.

541
00:44:16,446 --> 00:44:18,365
We found a policy
taken out with HA Life Insurance.

542
00:44:34,589 --> 00:44:36,424
SHOCK AS DOCTOR IN 30S DIES
IN SUSPECTED PROPOFOL SELF-INJECTION

543
00:44:37,258 --> 00:44:40,136
NFS REVEALS, "CAUSE OF DEATH WAS
PROPOFOL OVERDOSE, NO SIGNS OF FOUL PLAY"

544
00:44:42,389 --> 00:44:43,932
The doctor's name was Choi Young-ho.

545
00:44:44,015 --> 00:44:46,184
He had a whole life insurance policy
with HA Life Insurance,

546
00:44:46,267 --> 00:44:47,936
and the policy was set to pay out
500 million won

547
00:44:48,019 --> 00:44:50,522
to his then-partner, Han Seol-ah,
upon his death.

548
00:44:50,605 --> 00:44:52,440
His policy was canceled
before he died too.

549
00:44:53,024 --> 00:44:55,443
So she didn't
get this 500 million payout either?

550
00:44:57,278 --> 00:44:59,572
What's up with this woman?

551
00:45:00,240 --> 00:45:02,075
In any case, she didn't get the payout.

552
00:45:02,659 --> 00:45:05,703
Two people died after taking out
huge life insurance policies,

553
00:45:05,787 --> 00:45:07,205
and the beneficiary is the same person.

554
00:45:07,914 --> 00:45:09,707
As a former police captain,
do you not find it suspicious?

555
00:45:09,791 --> 00:45:12,460
That's why it's even less of our concern,

556
00:45:12,544 --> 00:45:15,004
unless the police take an interest in it.

557
00:45:15,088 --> 00:45:18,007
Jeez, you've become a corporate man
through and through.

558
00:45:19,259 --> 00:45:20,844
Hand this over to Detective Gong.

559
00:45:20,927 --> 00:45:23,346
Don't bother with things
that don't count for your performance.

560
00:45:24,889 --> 00:45:25,723
Hey, Cha-cha.

561
00:45:27,100 --> 00:45:28,393
Cha-cha!

562
00:45:30,103 --> 00:45:33,231
I don't know why
this reminds me of that movie.

563
00:45:38,820 --> 00:45:39,779
What are you doing?

564
00:45:47,328 --> 00:45:48,955
Don't you know
Basic Instinct
, Mr. Koo?

565
00:45:49,038 --> 00:45:52,500
Maybe Han Seol-ah is like Sharon Stone
in
Basic Instinct
.

566
00:45:52,584 --> 00:45:53,793
She uses her incredible beauty

567
00:45:53,877 --> 00:45:55,837
to seduce men
into taking out insurance policies

568
00:45:55,920 --> 00:45:57,755
before killing them without mercy!

569
00:46:04,304 --> 00:46:05,597
Should I just kill him?

570
00:46:07,974 --> 00:46:09,350
An SIU investigator?

571
00:46:09,434 --> 00:46:10,810
ION MENTAL CLINIC

572
00:46:10,894 --> 00:46:14,230
I'm not sure why I need to disclose
a deceased person's personal life.

573
00:46:15,732 --> 00:46:16,566
You're not even with the police.

574
00:46:18,109 --> 00:46:20,153
Then do you know who Han Seol-ah is?

575
00:46:22,655 --> 00:46:24,491
We have to maintain
doctor-patient confidentiality--

576
00:46:24,574 --> 00:46:26,367
So she was a patient here.

577
00:46:28,411 --> 00:46:30,580
In any case, I have nothing to tell you.

578
00:46:49,974 --> 00:46:50,808
Hello.

579
00:46:55,730 --> 00:46:58,274
Man, I'm hungry.

580
00:47:07,742 --> 00:47:08,785
Ms. Kim Mi-yeon?

581
00:47:10,662 --> 00:47:13,289
You know something about Ms. Han Seol-ah
and Dr. Choi Young-ho, don't you?

582
00:47:16,960 --> 00:47:18,127
I need a few minutes of your time.

583
00:47:22,423 --> 00:47:23,341
It'll cost you.

584
00:47:33,601 --> 00:47:34,769
Depression?

585
00:47:37,522 --> 00:47:39,148
I guess she was hurting badly

586
00:47:39,732 --> 00:47:41,109
after breaking up with her boyfriend.

587
00:47:45,488 --> 00:47:48,700
Are you saying
she dated someone before Mr. Choi?

588
00:47:49,284 --> 00:47:50,118
Are you kidding me?

589
00:47:50,702 --> 00:47:53,496
Of course, she dated someone before him.
She's gorgeous.

590
00:47:54,122 --> 00:47:57,500
Dr. Choi was so head over heels for her
that he even dumped his girlfriend.

591
00:48:02,589 --> 00:48:03,423
Anyway,

592
00:48:03,506 --> 00:48:06,426
an old heartbreak
is healed through new love.

593
00:48:06,509 --> 00:48:08,303
It's one of those cliché stories.

594
00:48:08,386 --> 00:48:11,764
But I guess she failed at healing,
seeing how things turned out for Dr. Choi.

595
00:48:15,643 --> 00:48:16,603
Then, by any chance,

596
00:48:17,520 --> 00:48:20,982
do you know anything more
about Han Seol-ah's previous boyfriend?

597
00:48:22,275 --> 00:48:23,192
He died.

598
00:48:24,110 --> 00:48:25,570
I think it was somewhere
in the Middle East.

599
00:48:25,653 --> 00:48:27,989
I heard he died in a terrorist attack.

600
00:48:30,658 --> 00:48:31,743
Are you sure he's dead?

601
00:48:32,660 --> 00:48:33,745
Yes.

602
00:48:33,828 --> 00:48:35,121
I mean, it's uncommon.

603
00:48:35,204 --> 00:48:36,914
A terrorist attack in the Middle East.

604
00:48:50,136 --> 00:48:52,472
HAN SEOL-AH MEETING WITH CHAIR KIM,
AUCTION TEAM AFTERNOON MEETING

605
00:48:54,140 --> 00:48:55,391
HAN SEOL-AH BUSINESS TRIP

606
00:49:01,773 --> 00:49:03,900
LEASE SIGNING FOR LUEN PALACE UNIT 702

607
00:49:06,069 --> 00:49:08,613
Did you know Kim Yun-ji went to see
Yoon Seung-jae at his restaurant?

608
00:49:08,696 --> 00:49:10,031
On the day before the accident, at that.

609
00:49:12,492 --> 00:49:13,868
Why did those two meet?

610
00:49:17,413 --> 00:49:19,749
LEASE SIGNING FOR LUEN PALACE UNIT 702

611
00:49:28,800 --> 00:49:29,967
You're still here?

612
00:49:31,969 --> 00:49:32,887
Yeah.

613
00:49:34,389 --> 00:49:35,264
What are you doing?

614
00:49:36,265 --> 00:49:39,060
Oh, I was just organizing some files.

615
00:49:40,186 --> 00:49:42,355
What brings you here at this hour?

616
00:49:45,817 --> 00:49:47,235
I wanted to ask you something.

617
00:49:50,238 --> 00:49:53,324
Seung-jae once mentioned
that he took out a life insurance policy…

618
00:49:55,618 --> 00:49:57,370
and named you as the beneficiary.

619
00:49:59,831 --> 00:50:00,957
By any chance…

620
00:50:04,085 --> 00:50:05,294
did you receive the payout?

621
00:50:08,798 --> 00:50:10,216
Why do you ask?

622
00:50:13,010 --> 00:50:14,387
Tell me. I need to know.

623
00:50:17,640 --> 00:50:19,100
Come on, not you too.

624
00:50:21,602 --> 00:50:22,478
Did you…

625
00:50:24,897 --> 00:50:25,773
really love…

626
00:50:27,233 --> 00:50:28,317
Seung-jae?

627
00:50:38,578 --> 00:50:39,412
Seol-ah.

628
00:50:39,954 --> 00:50:42,373
What do you want me to say?

629
00:50:42,957 --> 00:50:44,959
Don't you think
you're being too cruel to me?

630
00:50:45,585 --> 00:50:46,627
No, I didn't mean--

631
00:50:46,711 --> 00:50:47,587
Of all people,

632
00:50:49,046 --> 00:50:50,465
I thought you were on my side.

633
00:50:53,634 --> 00:50:55,178
This is all our friendship
amounts to, huh?

634
00:51:20,036 --> 00:51:22,663
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

635
00:51:22,747 --> 00:51:24,415
INSURANCE FOR THE ONES YOU LOVE

636
00:51:56,072 --> 00:51:59,700
YOON SEUNG-JAE, CHOI YOUNG-HO,
A THIRD MAN?

637
00:52:01,911 --> 00:52:03,955
HAN SEOL-AH

638
00:52:26,060 --> 00:52:28,813
"TERRORIST BOMB ATTACK IN SYRIA
KILLS KOREAN MAN"

639
00:52:31,232 --> 00:52:32,108
1 KOREAN AID WORKER KILLED

640
00:52:32,191 --> 00:52:34,068
On the 14th in Raqqa, Syria,

641
00:52:34,151 --> 00:52:37,113
a terrorist attack was carried out
by an armed group called IS,

642
00:52:37,196 --> 00:52:39,615
claiming the life of a Korean aid worker

643
00:52:39,699 --> 00:52:41,784
and adding to the grief of this tragedy.

644
00:52:41,868 --> 00:52:46,539
The attack took place in an area
controlled by IS-affiliated militants,

645
00:52:46,622 --> 00:52:51,127
and reports say a powerful explosion
killed dozens of people.

646
00:52:52,670 --> 00:52:56,132
THE DECEASED WAS A KOREAN NGO WORKER
PROVIDING HUMANITARIAN AID…

647
00:52:56,716 --> 00:52:58,467
They consigned it under my name?

648
00:52:58,551 --> 00:53:01,721
Yes, they insisted
that it be delivered to you.

649
00:53:11,105 --> 00:53:12,440
It's called…

650
00:53:13,357 --> 00:53:15,067
An Orphan from Syria.

651
00:54:38,067 --> 00:54:38,943
Nice painting.

652
00:54:42,863 --> 00:54:44,782
Unauthorized personnel
aren't allowed in here.

653
00:54:44,865 --> 00:54:45,866
Please leave.

654
00:54:49,537 --> 00:54:50,538
Seven years ago,

655
00:54:51,664 --> 00:54:53,958
there was a woman who had a boyfriend.

656
00:54:54,917 --> 00:54:56,961
The man worked
for an international relief organization

657
00:54:57,044 --> 00:54:58,963
that often went into
dangerous conflict zones.

658
00:55:00,756 --> 00:55:04,051
He took out a life insurance policy
for the woman he loved.

659
00:55:04,135 --> 00:55:05,219
The policy

660
00:55:06,012 --> 00:55:08,180
was set to pay out 200 million won
upon his death.

661
00:55:11,934 --> 00:55:14,145
He died in a terrorist attack in Syria.

662
00:55:18,899 --> 00:55:21,902
But the woman
couldn't collect the payout. Why?

663
00:55:23,863 --> 00:55:26,323
Because he suddenly canceled the policy.

664
00:55:28,367 --> 00:55:29,994
She must've been devastated.

665
00:55:31,120 --> 00:55:32,288
She lost her lover

666
00:55:33,247 --> 00:55:34,457
and the payout.

667
00:55:36,250 --> 00:55:39,628
Following the incident,
she became depressed and sought therapy.

668
00:55:41,589 --> 00:55:44,383
But who knows if she was
actually depressed or just pretending?

669
00:55:46,886 --> 00:55:47,762
And this is when

670
00:55:47,845 --> 00:55:49,930
a certain psychiatrist
makes his appearance.

671
00:55:50,014 --> 00:55:52,933
He fell in love with the woman
while trying to help her heal.

672
00:55:53,017 --> 00:55:54,351
ION MENTAL CLINIC
DIRECTOR CHOI YOUNG-HO

673
00:55:55,811 --> 00:55:58,898
He also took out a life insurance policy
and named her the beneficiary.

674
00:55:59,482 --> 00:56:00,733
But a few days before his suicide,

675
00:56:01,609 --> 00:56:02,818
he canceled the policy.

676
00:56:05,571 --> 00:56:07,698
The restaurant CEO
who got into an accident on the river

677
00:56:07,782 --> 00:56:09,575
also canceled his policy before he died.

678
00:56:13,996 --> 00:56:17,333
The woman lost three men
but gained nothing.

679
00:56:19,752 --> 00:56:22,463
But unlike her,
I gained something from these three cases.

680
00:56:24,173 --> 00:56:25,800
If you love Han Seol-ah…

681
00:56:28,636 --> 00:56:29,637
you die.

682
00:56:31,972 --> 00:56:32,973
And that's a fact.

683
00:56:41,816 --> 00:56:44,485
I'm sure those men wanted to save
the deeply hurt woman.

684
00:56:44,568 --> 00:56:46,946
You see, men tend to go blind

685
00:56:47,029 --> 00:56:48,948
once they fall in love.

686
00:56:49,031 --> 00:56:51,992
That's why they gave their all to her,
even their lives.

687
00:56:54,411 --> 00:56:55,496
In those men's eyes,

688
00:56:56,914 --> 00:56:58,999
she must've seemed like such a pitiful,

689
00:57:00,459 --> 00:57:02,169
helpless woman.

690
00:57:08,425 --> 00:57:09,927
Then, in your eyes,

691
00:57:10,845 --> 00:57:13,013
how does that woman appear right now?

692
00:57:30,239 --> 00:57:31,198
I'm not sure.

693
00:57:33,534 --> 00:57:34,618
I can't really see her.

694
00:57:47,882 --> 00:57:48,841
Can you see her now?

695
00:57:52,553 --> 00:57:54,096
That pitiful woman…

696
00:57:58,601 --> 00:58:00,853
Does she look like the kind of woman

697
00:58:01,812 --> 00:58:03,480
who wants to be saved by another man?

698
00:58:15,242 --> 00:58:17,286
You said anyone who loves me ends up dead.

699
00:58:18,245 --> 00:58:20,623
You talk as if
you know everything about me.

700
00:58:25,711 --> 00:58:27,379
Then tell me.

701
00:58:29,006 --> 00:58:30,507
Who's next?

702
00:58:32,051 --> 00:58:33,260
Next?

703
00:58:41,352 --> 00:58:43,395
The next man who'll fall in love…

704
00:58:47,441 --> 00:58:48,484
with Han Seol-ah.

705
00:59:06,961 --> 00:59:10,256
SPECIAL THANKS TO LEE ELIJAH
AND HA SEOKJIN FOR THEIR APPEARANCE

706
00:59:33,570 --> 00:59:35,489
The pain of becoming a mistress.

707
00:59:36,198 --> 00:59:38,867
The man who doesn't deliver
on his promise.

708
00:59:38,951 --> 00:59:40,744
What did you gain
from the deaths of those men?

709
00:59:41,203 --> 00:59:43,747
Does knowing that change anything?

710
00:59:44,915 --> 00:59:46,250
I think I know where it is.

711
00:59:48,877 --> 00:59:50,587
It felt like I was falling in love.

712
00:59:50,671 --> 00:59:53,716
So? Did you decide on your next man?

713
00:59:54,341 --> 00:59:57,219
Step aside if you don't want to cause
any misunderstandings.

714
00:59:58,887 --> 01:00:00,014
Who exactly are you?

715
01:00:01,098 --> 01:00:02,725
Why did you approach me?

716
01:00:05,686 --> 01:00:07,688
Subtitle: Jenny Kim

